main event: An unidentified object was observed in Miamisburg, Ohio on August 15, 1965.
interesting points: The object was visible for over one hour and displayed erratic motion,The observer described the object as very bright or brighter than a star,There was no physical evidence found at the sighting location,The sighting conclusion was classified as an Aero (star/planet),This case is recorded as Project Blue Book report 10073.
